headline: 2 Reasons to Like PG and 1 to Stay Skeptical
summary: Procter & Gamble has followed the market’s trajectory closely. The stock is down 6.2% to $168.47 per share over the past six months while the S&P 500 has lost 2.2%. This may have investors wondering how to approach the situation.
